1
00:02:40,680 --> 00:02:42,280
Boiled Chinese sausage.

2
00:02:43,200 --> 00:02:44,800
Steamed fish with curry paste.

3
00:02:44,880 --> 00:02:46,560
I'm getting hungry listening to you.

4
00:02:46,640 --> 00:02:48,680
Let's get some rice.

5
00:02:49,800 --> 00:02:50,960
Hey.

6
00:02:51,040 --> 00:02:53,680
This is for Madam Orn only.
There's none for you.

7
00:02:53,760 --> 00:02:55,040
Cheewa.

8
00:02:57,920 --> 00:02:59,120
My gosh.

9
00:03:00,680 --> 00:03:02,960
Enjoy your time together in hell, Dalad.

10
00:03:04,200 --> 00:03:05,280
Dalad!

11
00:03:06,680 --> 00:03:10,320
Please be alive, Dalad.
Please find him as soon as possible.

12
00:03:12,120 --> 00:03:13,240
Mr. Nava is at home.

13
00:03:13,320 --> 00:03:14,760
So why isn't Muslin picking up my calls?

14
00:03:14,840 --> 00:03:16,760
-Hello.
-You dumbass.

15
00:03:16,840 --> 00:03:19,440
I'm so stupid.
I keep calling the wrong number.

16
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:22,120
How much credit have I wasted now?

17
00:03:26,680 --> 00:03:29,360
Why are you here alone?

18
00:03:29,440 --> 00:03:30,960
Where is Saruj?

19
00:03:32,680 --> 00:03:34,120
He's gone to Chiang Mai.

20
00:03:34,200 --> 00:03:36,240
What? What did you say?

21
00:03:36,880 --> 00:03:39,960
He asked me to tell you
that he was worried about Muslin,

22
00:03:40,040 --> 00:03:41,200
so he flew to Chiang Mai.

23
00:03:41,760 --> 00:03:44,240
He'll stay the night and return tomorrow.

24
00:03:45,160 --> 00:03:46,880
Gosh.

25
00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:51,000
Thank you.

26
00:04:02,600 --> 00:04:08,040
CHIANG MAI

27
00:04:12,720 --> 00:04:13,680
Thank you.

28
00:04:13,760 --> 00:04:14,600
Mus.

29
00:04:16,040 --> 00:04:16,920
Muslin.

30
00:04:20,680 --> 00:04:21,959
Mr. Saruj.

31
00:04:22,040 --> 00:04:24,160
-Hello.
-Hello.

32
00:04:24,240 --> 00:04:26,360
Is Mus here? Has something happened?

33
00:04:26,920 --> 00:04:29,840
She's fine. What are you doing here?

34
00:04:31,680 --> 00:04:33,280
Why didn't you pick up my calls?

35
00:04:34,440 --> 00:04:35,400
Well,

36
00:04:35,480 --> 00:04:37,360
I had my phone turned off.

37
00:04:37,440 --> 00:04:39,560
I just wanted some peace and quiet.

38
00:04:40,120 --> 00:04:41,120
You had me worried.

39
00:04:41,200 --> 00:04:43,120
I thought
Mr. Nava had done something to you.

40
00:04:44,440 --> 00:04:45,440
Are you okay?

41
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:47,240
He still hasn't found you, right?

42
00:04:47,840 --> 00:04:50,560
You came here
because you were worried about me?

43
00:04:50,640 --> 00:04:51,760
That's right.

44
00:04:52,880 --> 00:04:57,000
Mr. Nava is crazy.
He could have done anything.

45
00:04:59,680 --> 00:05:01,440
I'm so happy.

46
00:05:02,120 --> 00:05:04,760
I'm happy
that I still mean something to you.

47
00:05:16,240 --> 00:05:18,160
This seems to be a nice place to live.

48
00:05:18,240 --> 00:05:19,280
Yes.

49
00:05:19,840 --> 00:05:23,360
The house I bought is under construction,
so I'm renting this place for now.

50
00:05:23,440 --> 00:05:26,800
Now that I have a house
where my mom is safe from Nava,

51
00:05:26,880 --> 00:05:28,640
I'm not worried anymore.

52
00:05:29,680 --> 00:05:31,840
Mr. Nava has gone quiet.

53
00:05:31,920 --> 00:05:33,680
He's probably moved on.

54
00:05:34,680 --> 00:05:39,480
I'll only be confident about that
when I see a divorce certificate.

55
00:05:40,360 --> 00:05:41,320
That's true.

56
00:05:43,760 --> 00:05:47,520
How are things between you and Cheewan?
We've never talked about this.

57
00:05:48,240 --> 00:05:49,800
As you know,

58
00:05:49,880 --> 00:05:52,160
I've told my parents about her.

59
00:05:52,240 --> 00:05:54,040
Our families are very close.

60
00:05:54,800 --> 00:05:58,200
Now, I only have to wait three years
for her to graduate.

61
00:06:00,280 --> 00:06:01,880
Three years?

62
00:06:01,960 --> 00:06:03,960
Since you're not getting married soon,

63
00:06:04,040 --> 00:06:06,560
does it mean I still have a chance

64
00:06:06,640 --> 00:06:08,960
in these three years?

65
00:06:09,040 --> 00:06:10,200
Mus.

66
00:06:10,680 --> 00:06:12,760
I'm going to be blunt.

67
00:06:12,840 --> 00:06:17,360
I still hope to get back to the point
we were at many years ago.

68
00:06:19,720 --> 00:06:21,240
I want to marry you.

69
00:06:23,120 --> 00:06:24,120
Well…

70
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:36,280
If you want me to apologize…

71
00:06:39,240 --> 00:06:40,800
then I'm sorry.

72
00:06:42,160 --> 00:06:46,240
I was wrong for ditching
the thing that was most valuable to me.

73
00:06:51,520 --> 00:06:54,360
Can we start over, Saruj?

74
00:07:06,960 --> 00:07:09,120
Right now, you feel vulnerable,

75
00:07:09,200 --> 00:07:10,320
confused,

76
00:07:11,080 --> 00:07:12,240
and lonely.

77
00:07:12,320 --> 00:07:14,280
It's not a good time
to start a relationship.

78
00:07:21,840 --> 00:07:23,560
We got together when we were studying.

79
00:07:25,080 --> 00:07:29,600
We've known each other for ten years.
This isn't just a rebound. I'm sure.

80
00:07:31,720 --> 00:07:34,840
You're my first and only love.

81
00:07:37,720 --> 00:07:39,120
Please think about this.

82
00:07:40,480 --> 00:07:43,080
Our decade-long love and bond

83
00:07:44,200 --> 00:07:46,600
might be what you have been waiting for.

84
00:07:52,640 --> 00:07:54,640
I booked a hotel near the airport.

85
00:07:55,200 --> 00:07:56,640
I'm taking a flight in the morning

86
00:07:56,720 --> 00:07:57,960
so I can be back in time for work.

87
00:08:06,120 --> 00:08:07,240
Take care of yourself.

88
00:08:44,880 --> 00:08:46,440
Hi there.

89
00:08:46,520 --> 00:08:48,160
Here comes Tualek.

90
00:08:48,240 --> 00:08:51,440
She's here to see her dad and mom.

91
00:08:51,920 --> 00:08:53,240
She's here.

92
00:08:53,320 --> 00:08:55,800
You're smiling so sweetly.

93
00:08:56,280 --> 00:08:59,560
-Tualek, come here.
-Here you go. What?

94
00:08:59,640 --> 00:09:02,320
-I'm leaving for work soon.
-Go to your grandpa.

95
00:09:02,400 --> 00:09:05,080
Let him admire you first, dear.

96
00:09:05,840 --> 00:09:08,840
-I was here first.
-You're so adorable, dear.

97
00:09:08,920 --> 00:09:11,920
Can I use my rights as her dad?

98
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:13,880
I'm also a dad.

99
00:09:13,960 --> 00:09:15,320
I'm the dad of her mom.

100
00:09:15,400 --> 00:09:16,920
I'm above you.

101
00:09:22,360 --> 00:09:23,560
Cheewa.

102
00:09:23,640 --> 00:09:24,760
Yes?

103
00:09:24,840 --> 00:09:27,720
We have decided

104
00:09:27,800 --> 00:09:29,440
to raise her ourselves.

105
00:09:33,680 --> 00:09:36,520
Mom, please let me raise her.

106
00:09:37,080 --> 00:09:39,200
I'm afraid you'll get tired

107
00:09:39,280 --> 00:09:41,200
and won't have time for yourselves.

108
00:09:41,840 --> 00:09:42,680
That's right.

109
00:09:43,360 --> 00:09:45,160
She has parents,

110
00:09:45,240 --> 00:09:48,400
but you two are taking over our duty.

111
00:09:50,800 --> 00:09:51,880
Cheewa,

112
00:09:52,360 --> 00:09:56,000
why don't you raise her for a few years,
then return to your studies?

113
00:09:57,680 --> 00:09:59,360
And you too, Poom.

114
00:09:59,440 --> 00:10:02,320
You must advance your career.

115
00:10:02,400 --> 00:10:04,080
You're at an important age.

116
00:10:04,160 --> 00:10:06,600
You can't give up on it.

117
00:10:07,560 --> 00:10:09,880
Are you two going to take our child?

118
00:10:11,440 --> 00:10:12,400
-Yes.
-Yes.

119
00:10:16,240 --> 00:10:18,160
Chavit can run things better than me.

120
00:10:18,240 --> 00:10:19,760
He's the new generation.

121
00:10:21,200 --> 00:10:23,240
We're still strong.

122
00:10:23,320 --> 00:10:24,840
Raising a child is tiring.

123
00:10:25,400 --> 00:10:27,120
But it makes us very happy.

124
00:10:29,040 --> 00:10:30,040
Honey,

125
00:10:30,120 --> 00:10:32,040
does this remind you of the past

126
00:10:32,120 --> 00:10:35,160
when we were young
and bringing up children?

127
00:10:35,240 --> 00:10:36,560
Yes.

128
00:10:36,640 --> 00:10:38,600
It was tiring, but we were very happy.

129
00:10:41,920 --> 00:10:43,160
Cheewa.

130
00:10:43,240 --> 00:10:44,600
Thank you

131
00:10:44,680 --> 00:10:48,960
for having Tualek
to keep your dad and me company.

132
00:10:49,040 --> 00:10:54,200
When I was expecting her,
I thought she was an embarrassment,

133
00:10:54,760 --> 00:10:57,200
so I didn't dare consult
you both about it.

134
00:10:57,840 --> 00:11:00,520
I was so stupid back then.

135
00:11:01,960 --> 00:11:05,400
When in distress, people always assume

136
00:11:05,480 --> 00:11:06,640
that there is no solution,

137
00:11:06,720 --> 00:11:09,000
but every problem has a solution.

138
00:11:09,560 --> 00:11:10,880
And neither of us

139
00:11:10,960 --> 00:11:13,360
feels embarrassed
like you thought we would be.

140
00:11:14,400 --> 00:11:15,640
That's right, dear.

141
00:11:15,720 --> 00:11:17,040
Cheewa.

142
00:11:17,520 --> 00:11:20,280
Why don't you look at this
from another perspective?

143
00:11:20,360 --> 00:11:21,440
You see,

144
00:11:21,520 --> 00:11:24,880
a burden can turn into happiness,

145
00:11:24,960 --> 00:11:27,800
so long as you make sure
your mistake makes you stronger.

146
00:11:27,880 --> 00:11:29,280
Return to your studies, all right?

147
00:11:30,120 --> 00:11:33,000
Go back to pursue your dream

148
00:11:33,720 --> 00:11:35,440
and make it happen.

149
00:11:38,760 --> 00:11:40,600
Thank you, Mom,

150
00:11:41,480 --> 00:11:42,320
Dad.

151
00:11:42,400 --> 00:11:43,280
No worries.

152
00:11:49,320 --> 00:11:50,240
Okay.

153
00:11:51,480 --> 00:11:52,760
I won't tease you anymore.

154
00:11:55,040 --> 00:11:56,280
Let's not tease him anymore.

155
00:11:57,840 --> 00:11:59,560
All right, go to your dad.

156
00:11:59,640 --> 00:12:01,000
-Go to your dad.
-Can I hold her?

157
00:12:01,080 --> 00:12:03,440
-Go to your dad.
-Go now.

158
00:12:03,520 --> 00:12:05,360
Tualek.

159
00:12:08,080 --> 00:12:10,680
Come and play with me.

160
00:12:10,760 --> 00:12:12,680
You're crying.

161
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:15,160
What?

162
00:12:17,160 --> 00:12:18,120
She's asleep.

163
00:12:20,560 --> 00:12:21,560
You won't get to play with her then.

164
00:12:22,080 --> 00:12:24,320
-Honey.
-I'm so sorry, Poom.

165
00:12:25,160 --> 00:12:28,160
Stop teasing him already
and go to work. Go on.

166
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:31,480
See you later.

167
00:12:42,920 --> 00:12:45,160
We won't get to talk today.

168
00:12:54,360 --> 00:12:56,440
That day you asked me

169
00:12:57,000 --> 00:12:58,720
who the boy in the drawing was,

170
00:12:59,400 --> 00:13:00,760
and I didn't reply to you.

171
00:13:01,840 --> 00:13:03,640
I wasn't ready back then.

172
00:13:04,720 --> 00:13:06,480
But I'm confident now.

173
00:13:06,560 --> 00:13:08,840
Take a look at the name
of the boy in the drawing.

174
00:13:11,120 --> 00:13:12,880
I'LL BE YOUR PRINCE

175
00:13:15,080 --> 00:13:16,960
RONNAPOOM JUTATHEP

176
00:13:17,520 --> 00:13:18,400
Cheewa.

177
00:13:20,640 --> 00:13:22,040
I wrote it back then.

178
00:13:24,400 --> 00:13:26,480
Go to the next page.

179
00:13:32,120 --> 00:13:34,880
RONNAPOOM JUTATHEP

180
00:13:34,960 --> 00:13:37,120
I lied to you

181
00:13:37,200 --> 00:13:39,400
about not having feelings for you.

182
00:13:40,080 --> 00:13:42,400
Have you really
had a crush on me since then?

183
00:13:45,360 --> 00:13:46,360
You didn't

184
00:13:47,320 --> 00:13:49,040
just write my name on it recently,
did you?

185
00:13:55,680 --> 00:13:57,960
You weren't friendly with me,

186
00:13:58,040 --> 00:14:00,480
so I thought you hated me.

187
00:14:00,560 --> 00:14:02,280
Why didn't you tell me

188
00:14:02,880 --> 00:14:04,440
that you had a crush on me?

189
00:14:06,200 --> 00:14:08,800
Well, you were so cool,

190
00:14:08,880 --> 00:14:10,280
so I thought

191
00:14:11,040 --> 00:14:15,080
it was just a teenage crush
on a guy in uniform.

192
00:14:16,280 --> 00:14:18,760
As I grew up, I guess I forgot about you.

193
00:14:22,600 --> 00:14:25,280
But I've never drawn
a picture of another man.

194
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:32,360
Poncheewa likes me!

195
00:14:32,440 --> 00:14:33,640
Poncheewa loves me.

196
00:14:40,080 --> 00:14:41,640
You love me like a lover,

197
00:14:42,480 --> 00:14:43,880
not like a brother.

198
00:14:45,440 --> 00:14:47,280
Please lower your voice, Poom.

199
00:14:47,920 --> 00:14:49,560
It's embarrassing.

200
00:14:54,080 --> 00:14:55,800
Thank you for loving me.

201
00:15:08,720 --> 00:15:10,760
That's not a brotherly kiss.

202
00:15:15,280 --> 00:15:18,080
Poncheewa loves me!

203
00:15:18,160 --> 00:15:19,400
Poncheewa loves me!

204
00:15:19,480 --> 00:15:22,280
-Poncheewa loves--
-Poom, please lower your voice.

205
00:15:52,040 --> 00:15:54,560
Hey, Cheewan. Are you here to see me?

206
00:15:57,120 --> 00:15:58,240
What is it?

207
00:16:01,280 --> 00:16:02,520
You're not saying anything.

208
00:16:03,160 --> 00:16:04,600
Maybe you're here to see someone else.

209
00:16:07,960 --> 00:16:09,720
But I'm the only one here.

210
00:16:13,320 --> 00:16:14,560
You still won't say it.

211
00:16:15,480 --> 00:16:17,600
I guess there's something wrong
with your mouth.

212
00:16:18,400 --> 00:16:19,520
Let me check.

213
00:16:36,560 --> 00:16:38,400
There's nothing wrong with it.

214
00:16:41,320 --> 00:16:43,080
You still won't say it.

215
00:16:44,040 --> 00:16:45,920
If your mouth doesn't work properly,

216
00:16:47,160 --> 00:16:49,760
I think I'll have to use my mouth
to help you.

217
00:16:53,120 --> 00:16:54,640
Why are you just sitting there?

218
00:16:55,120 --> 00:16:56,320
Aren't you going to stop me?

219
00:17:02,520 --> 00:17:04,760
-Hey, are you crazy?
-Hey.

220
00:17:05,319 --> 00:17:07,240
Why don't you go and live in Chiang Mai?

221
00:17:07,319 --> 00:17:09,040
Just buy a house there with her

222
00:17:09,119 --> 00:17:10,480
since you're so worried about her.

223
00:17:10,560 --> 00:17:11,680
Hold on.

224
00:17:12,480 --> 00:17:14,079
I only went there for a day.

225
00:17:14,160 --> 00:17:16,280
I came back as soon as I'd talked to her.

226
00:17:16,359 --> 00:17:18,040
Nothing happened between us.

227
00:17:18,119 --> 00:17:20,440
Who asked you that? I don't want to know.

228
00:17:36,400 --> 00:17:39,480
-Gosh, take this.
-Wait.

229
00:17:39,560 --> 00:17:41,560
-Take this.
-Wait.

230
00:17:41,640 --> 00:17:42,680
You're crazy.

231
00:17:43,480 --> 00:17:44,800
I'm all wet now.

232
00:17:46,040 --> 00:17:47,280
It's cold in here.

233
00:17:47,360 --> 00:17:49,560
How can you swim in this weather?

234
00:17:52,560 --> 00:17:55,200
All right, I'll hug you.

235
00:17:55,280 --> 00:17:57,080
-Let go of me.
-Do you feel warm now?

236
00:17:57,960 --> 00:17:59,000
Let go.

237
00:17:59,720 --> 00:18:00,960
Be quiet first.

238
00:18:03,160 --> 00:18:05,200
I'm glad you're jealous.

239
00:18:08,200 --> 00:18:09,840
You're so worried about me.

240
00:18:10,400 --> 00:18:11,720
I'm so happy.

241
00:18:13,440 --> 00:18:15,160
Mrs. Mus lied to you.

242
00:18:15,240 --> 00:18:17,160
She intentionally ignored your calls.

243
00:18:17,840 --> 00:18:19,560
She wanted your attention.

244
00:18:20,480 --> 00:18:21,560
Yes.

245
00:18:22,200 --> 00:18:24,200
Is that all you have to say?

246
00:18:24,840 --> 00:18:26,720
This means you knew about it then.

247
00:18:27,840 --> 00:18:30,280
If you're afraid I'll get back together
with her,

248
00:18:31,240 --> 00:18:32,840
then tell me you love me.

249
00:18:35,200 --> 00:18:37,040
-That's got nothing to do with it.
-It does.

250
00:18:38,480 --> 00:18:41,520
If you say you love me,

251
00:18:42,360 --> 00:18:45,640
I'll keep my heart

252
00:18:46,320 --> 00:18:47,760
for you only.

253
00:18:51,840 --> 00:18:53,040
Let go.

254
00:18:53,920 --> 00:18:55,880
Didn't you say you were cold?

255
00:18:58,400 --> 00:19:00,600
My warm heart

256
00:19:01,160 --> 00:19:03,760
only has a place for you.

257
00:19:05,800 --> 00:19:06,920
Say it.

258
00:19:08,680 --> 00:19:10,080
Say that you love me.

259
00:19:23,160 --> 00:19:24,120
Hey.

260
00:19:24,600 --> 00:19:27,200
-Take this.
-Hey.

261
00:19:27,280 --> 00:19:29,600
Wait, Cheewan. I give up now.

262
00:19:30,880 --> 00:19:34,000
Did you go there just to annoy me?

263
00:19:35,200 --> 00:19:36,800
I'll remember this.

264
00:19:47,200 --> 00:19:49,360
Cheewan, where are you taking my clothes?

265
00:19:50,560 --> 00:19:52,000
Aren't you warm?

266
00:19:52,080 --> 00:19:55,680
Why would you need your clothes then?
Why don't you walk back like that?

267
00:19:56,720 --> 00:19:57,800
Hold on, Cheewan.

268
00:19:58,280 --> 00:20:01,080
It's cold. Bring them back.

269
00:20:01,160 --> 00:20:02,120
Cheewan.

270
00:20:17,240 --> 00:20:18,600
Kwan,

271
00:20:19,360 --> 00:20:21,720
please take care of Chat for me.

272
00:20:21,800 --> 00:20:25,160
Make sure you tame him, dear.

273
00:20:25,920 --> 00:20:26,880
Yes, ma'am.

274
00:20:29,520 --> 00:20:31,800
May your love be long-lasting

275
00:20:31,880 --> 00:20:34,600
and stable.

276
